The paper focuses on studying biological neural networks from an algorithmic perspective, specifically in the context of winner-take-all (WTA) computation. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of algorithmic primitives in a biologically plausible model, which could also place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the WTA problem as a basic building block in many tasks, which could suggest a connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
